Found to be an easy marker, took CMN2180 with him, and found his lectures to be somewhat useless. If you read the textbook, you would either find regurgitation, or you's sit in class and watch YouTube videos for half of it. Felt more like he had to fulfill class hours instead of actually wanting to teach. Funny, good guy, didn't like the class.

Strangelove for me inspired me to be involved in my education. His assignments encouraged self-expressions and focused on personal passions. His lectures were easy to pay attention to and intersting. He is a solid prof that I would 100% take a class with again. The only complaint  you have to be on top of assignment right from the get go.
worst prof ever! Avoid! avoid!!!

Dr. Strangelove is overall a good professor. Although his lectures may be a bit unorthodox, he genuinely wants to see his students succeed. Start working on projects early - for the ad campaigns his critiques and suggestions on where to improve gave students a chance to review their work, thus receiving a better grade! He's fair and knows his stuff

Strangelove is a funny guy. He does want students to succeed. He reminds students every class to get work done in advance. Start your project the first week of class - it will be easier to shape and edit closer to the deadline. And DO show your work to the class!! Feedback is super helpful!

This is my 4th class with Strangelove and I love his lectures! I learned a lot, even if I don't remember it. Very inspirational and passionate about communications. Not always clear during lectures, but readings are helpful! Gives hints throughout lectures about exams.
As a person he's very nice and willing to help out students. However he tends to ramble and go off on side notes, it's hard to pay attention.
Worst prof ever!!! Avoid him!!!!

He's a very eccentric person which was funny at first but It quickly began to ruin lectures because of the lack of focus. The tests were easy because they were essentially the slides but the class lacked cohesion and a clear focus. At times I felt like his opinions were the course material and we had to agree to pass the class.

He is very.. Interesting... His lectures are very unique and taking his class is an experience. He tends to go waaaayyyyyy off subject and sometimes it makes it hard to concentrate on the actual class. His exams are easy since they're basically the lecture slides.

Expects you to memorize his entire book, asks super vague questions that are impossible to distinguish between right and wrong answers. All M/C exams. Learned nothing about media ethics, the entire course is about anti-capitalism and promoting his book. Avoid!

You will have to memorize his textbook word for word if you want to do will because his exams are all multiple choice and he picks the most random, obscure phrases from the book that have absolutely no context. He'll give questions like "concept a __ affect concept b" and the answers will be may, could, might. So nit picky.
His lectures are very interesting, you would not want to miss a class with him. Evaluations include a midterm and a final exam (both multiple choice).
Strangelove is an amazing prof, he's so nice and helpful. This class was super fun, interesting and easy!

Strangelove I took for multiple CMN courses hence why I wrote CMN000. If I could have Strangelove for all of my courses, I truly would. He is very inspiring and passionate and knowledgable. The best way to succeed in his class is to attend every class ready to take notes. Read all texts assigned. And open your mind to learning. Great prof great man

Very easy class and very interesting, but there's one main problem, he takes his political views very seriously. He claims to be a teacher who enjoys discussion and debates over topics, but he fills his tests with questions which are based off of his political views, and you will get a poor grade if you do not take his views as facts.

Very easy course, very easy marker. You have to read the textbook, but besides that it is an easy A. Quotes from the text were shown on his slides, and then appeared on the exams, which are predictable and straightforward. I actually learned a lot in his course, which I found pretty interesting. Was scared bc of the reviews here, but he's a peach!

Strangelove is a great professor. He is very inspirational and convincing in his argumentation of the different problems we face in todays world. In this course, he talks about a plethora of subjects that are very relevant to people who care about the state of political and enviromental affairs in the world. Read the book and get an A.

Strangelove is the best professor I have had in my 3 years at uOttawa. He is a great speaker and when he gets to his points he can be quite convincing. He made the course very interesting and relevant, even using current reports written in news papers. Easy A if you read the textbook and do the presentation or video well. Highly recommend.

I don't know why he is so poorly rated on here because he is a great prof! His lectures are very enjoyable and he is really funny! His midterm and final are easy if you do the readings and pay attention in class. His project is a bit ambiguous and he is a bit hard when marking them but give a lot of examples & it's a fun project. Highly recommend!!

You can tell he is passionate about teaching and wants students to do well. If you spoke during class he would thank you for your contribution after class and overall is just a very nice and funny prof. He can sometimes get off topic and can be hard to follow but if you go to class and pay attention to his lectures they are not too hard to follow.

Prof. Strangelove is a witty, fun professor. For Media Industries, he started off a little confusing early in the semester, but towards each exam he gave EXACTLY what was needed to pass, example questions from lectures being on the exam and all. His quirky nature definitely is a plus for me. Makes the sometimes dry material bare-able. Recommended!

if I wanted to watch YouTube for an hour I would do that at home. I don't need a doctor to type funny videos into the search bar for me, let alone pay tuition. He would start every class with a five minute YouTube clip. He'd lose track of time and before you know it he's cramming an hour lecture into fifteen minutes

Pros: - Easy A if you just show up to 75% of classes, read the book, and take note of the things he repeats.  - ALL classes consist of blog entries, creation of videos (group), final essay (just agree with his arguments) Cons:  - You wont learn much - Attendance is a must - Tries to make the simple theories complicated by using unneeded big words.

I had him for 3 classes in 1 semester. Had his class 6 times in total. Attendance matters even if he says it doesn't. His lectures are him picking points from his own book to ramble on about. Computers are forbidden. The most unorganized man I have ever met who tries his hardest to be inappropriate. Nice guy but very annoying as a prof.

Gets off topic very easily, and when he is actually teaching you have no idea what he is taking about, nice guy one on one (outside of class) Course is based on his book that he wrote. Book is worst then his lecture and a difficult read. * AVOID *
Charming man. Rambles on and on, but at least hes informative and interesting.

Thought it would be an easy class, totally wrong. But it was because he made it way harder than it needed to be. he talks forever about nothing and then all the random stuff he said ends up on the exam with no warning. The textbook is one that he wrote and has nothing to do with the subject of the course. It is more like an novel-length essay.

Mixed feelings. The content is fairly easy to understand however his tests are hard. It's a brief introduction to media studies then the study of his philosophies (in his book). The book is dense and irrelevant as the material for an 'intro to media studies course'  Overall he's a decent proff but the course focuses on his book too much.
He was actually helpful if you go talk to him but his lectures are very unclear. IF he gives a study guide it'll be very similar to the actual exams.

I am at a loss for why he is rated so poorly on here! If you go to class, do the readings, and then study the terms that he sends out by email before his tests, it's an easy A. As an English major who is used to studying thousands of pages of content, and writing an essay for my exams, this class was a breeze. He has three multiple choice tests...

Strangelove is probably a great guy outside of class, and probably an awesome guy to talk one-on-one with but a class of 300 people is clearly not suited to his teaching style. It's also evident that he likes to go off on tangents, which doesn't help as each lecture is only an hour long. Tests are ridiculously difficult as well. AVOID AT ALL COSTS.

He's eccentric and tries very hard to be different. Though he might seem engaging at first, his lectures are disorganized and have no structure at all. He often goes off topic to go on a tangent;very confusing because then we're left wondering what parts are part of the lecture vs his personal opinions. Tests are"choose the MOST correct answer"Hard

He rambles and is very unclear. He goes off on tangents that are absolutely horrendous. Had to make his second midterm easier cause everyone failed the first one due to his unclarity. Shows weird videos.

It's funny how he comes on this site to rate himself positively! He should stop caring what others think of him and improve his skills! Nice man, great life lessons. Just repeats his material too much. He makes his exams super tricky and doesn't let you see them after. His book is outdated now and he knows it. BOOK IS A MUST READ 4 A DECENT MARK!

By far one of the most interesting profs Ive ever had.  You can tell that he really cares about his students (he always tries to learn your name and makes funny comments). Also gives great life lessons! definitely a class worth taking. But be sure to work hard! read the required material and don't skip class!

I don't know how he got this job. I highly regret taking his class because I have not learned a single thing. His exams are all about irrelevant facts from his book or his opinion on something, even if it's wrong. I am so disappointed and feel completely ripped off. I am a straight A student but he killed my GPA. Never take a class with him!!!

Prof. Strangelove tends to go off-topic during his lectures, but I find his ideas engaging. He often uses lectures as a platform to speak of the evils of capitalism and empire to students who may be emerging from the home bubble. He's not wrong, but it's often not quite within direct scope of the course material. Read the book if you want to pass.

He seems like a nice enough man, but he tries to hard to be eccentric and is highly disorganized.  Uses long, pretentious words in his lectures and his textbook when concepts can be described very simply.  His tests contain grammar mistakes and multiple answers for the same question. With an average of 90% in other classes, I got 70%  in this one.

The guy is funny, and I like him as a person. However he is a really terrible educator. His lectures are all over the place. You never know what you should be taking notes on, or what to study. He is extremely disorganized. His powerpoints aren't clear, mind you he never actually finishes them because he just rambles on about himself.

He is very passionate and has a unique teaching style. His lectures aren't very organized, and he didn't give a rubric for the presentation, but the content is interesting and he genuinely wants his students to do well. His MC exams can be tough but he gives very obvious hints in class. We had a couple pot lucks in class - he tries to make it fun.

I've never met a prof that is so passionate about what he's teaching. He also doesn't treat you like a number, he generally wants to get to know his students. His exams really aren't that hard at all and he often hints on what you will be tested on. I really recommend his classes.

His train of thought is erratic and hard to follow. He confuses names/people and forgets things easily. You have to rely mostly on the books he wrote in order to do well in the class. Class was useful only when he hinted at what may be important for the midterm/exam. Don't know about this guy.
Great teacher, material is interesting and his test aren't difficult, as long as you go to class you should be good! Not a lot of readings either!

Strangelove is a very passionate educator and is very knowledgeable about the subject. The exams were mostly textbook based so reading all chapters is essential. At times it was difficult to follow what he was saying because he tends to ramble. However, he is a funny and energetic professor that attempts to make learning fun.

Easily one of my favourite profs. You show up, listen, take notes, and you walk away with a solid mark. He makes it very clear what to look at in the text for exams. There are 2 midterms and a final. This way my 3rd class with him, and he was the same every time. Don't hate the Strangelove

He tries so hard to be weird and eccentric, too hard. His lectures are a waste of time, he rambles, goes completely off topic & read passages out of his own textbook (which is awful). His midterms and exams consists of minor details mentioned in a line of the text and barely anything even mentioned in the lecture. Thanks for nothing Stranglove

Say what you will about the guy, but I feel like everyone should take a Strangelove course for the experience. He's very charismatic and... eccentric (he tries hard at it). He gives excellent lectures; despite the tangents, I could listen to him for hours. That said, he can spend an hour explaining something that I could sum up in a sentence.

Although Strangelove is eccentric, there is a no computer/tech. rule in his class, therefore for 3hrs you must listen carefully & write notes out by hand. Clarity was hard, because sometimes he would go on irrelevant rants. Read both texts,& attend lectures to improve grades. Helpful, and full of insight. Class atmosphere was light and fun.

Lectures are interesting but really unorganized. You need to read the textbook to figure out what is important and what you will be tested on. I found the multiple choice exams to be pretty easy but you definitely need to come to class and read the text critically if you want to do well. He's very eccentric but keeps things interesting.

He is a passionate professor that speaks truth about society and our place in the world. Although eccentric, he is what a University professor is supposed to be like, eccentric, slightly introvert and very caught up in thought. If you want to be better at critical thinking take a Strangelove course. If you want instruction... go to college.
BEST PROFESSOR EVER!!

I have now had Strangelove 3 times in my 4 years at U of O. My first class with him was horribly disorganized, however he has changed his teaching methods a great deal since. His classes are now well structured and he emphasizes what is important for the exams. His classes are interesting and fun! I recommend taking his class.

it's my last semester of undergrad and he is the worst prof I've ever had. lectures are completely disorganized, structure is pathetic and assignments are useless. it is hard to avoid taking him if youre in comms, but try.

Probably one of the worst profs I have had in my 3 years as a university student. I had all As in my assignments and ended up with a C+ as my final grade (although I am sure I did well on the final). I asked on several occasions to see my exam and he did not respond. And too crazy for my taste.

Wow, I didn't expect such negative reviews. I found Strangelove's class really interesting and completely different from all my other courses. He is laid back and fun unlike many profs at uOttawa. Managed to keep me awake at 8:30 in the morning. I didn't do as well as I thought I would given my interest and studying, but I enjoyed the class.

The most ridiculous prof. Always late to class, talks off the top of his head, and takes "non mandatory" attendance. Overall the class is a joke and a waste of time, he doesn't say anything different from what is in the textbooks. Not worth wasting your time on

People seem to be after him on this website. Despite all this negative feedback I've had him multiple times. He DOES respond to your e-mails, he DOES follow a structure in class (if you read the required readings you'll notice it's chapter by chapter), and he IS a good prof. By not going to class you're wasting your money. It's worth it so just go!

Seems like everyone who hates Strangelove has found this site.Though he is eccentric, why are you all complaining? 15 mark blog, 35 mark video doc which is a pice of cake then a final exam that is no more then 2 essay questions. Think you guys need to evaluate yourselves as students instead of Strangelove as a prof!! GREAT PROF!!

Everybody on hear seems to really have it agains't Dr Strangelove. He's a great prof, very helpful, knows a lot and makes the class interesting. The textbook he uses are very insightful and he's a fair grader- if you put the effort, you'll be rewarded. Seriously one of the best profs i have had at u of O, very knowledgable and crazy :)

A lot of bad comments concerning strangelove but most of them also consist of "Never went to class it was a waste of time". It's not, he has good insight and though a lot of it is left wing rants he is a very good prof. If ur in the CMN dpt. you have to at least try one class with him

4th year student here; 8.2 GPA. He has got to be one of the worst profs on campus.I did well in his class & odds are you will too, but he should NOT be teaching. He is rarely prepared, often WRONG about core concepts, uses class time to discuss his private life, & makes inappropriate comments. I felt like he brought down my morale AND my I.Q.

HORRIBLE! self obsessed. Uses his own books, the attendance is mandatory and if you miss 2-3 classes, he will make sure you either fail or get a D! Attending lectures is useless so basically you are just stuck in his class! I would actually change my course schedule after 2nd year if I knew he is teaching the prereq and take it later!
Have had him for two classes. Hands down the worst professor I've had. He teaches a lot of classes but avoid if you can. If you can't, reference him A LOT in your exam and you'll probably do fine.

He seemed like a fun and nice prof, and was an entertainging prof. However, the exam was based solely on oour ability to recall terms (not even theories, just terms). Lots of people didn't or almost didn't pass. He didn't even bother to say how many terms he wanted, but explained away low marks with "you didn't use enough terms" to several students
ABSOLUTELY Terrible.

Classes with him:  1st: A-      2nd: D     3rd: B+   He only cares about his lectures content. What content? I tried to take notes, was left with blank pages. I'm an A student and he wouldn't explain my D or meet with me. The 'fake' attendance isn't fake,  he uses it to guide himself. I attended all classes but didn't write my name to test it...D
Pointless class, says the same thing over and over again. No new insight on any topics. He insists on pushing his own view on everyone and if you dont agree you wont do well in the class!

I guess it's hate it or love it with professor Strangelove. Too bad for him it looks like it's mostly hate that goes to this website. But he's a cool guy and good teacher. Most people here don't get him and mistake his style for arrogance. But his lectures are very deep, though sometimes repetitive, it helps it sink in. Loved the class, awesome guy

This guy is a JOKE - so glad I am done with U of O and do not have to endure his BS any longer. Looking back on each class I was required to attend(although I rarely went since it was a terrible use of my time...) I cannot help but think "hmm.. well, there goes three hours of my life I will never get back." This guy is a clown and a DISGRACE!

Strangelove is not your average prof with serious structure or who teaches right out of the book.  He does however have opinions and teaches the REAL WORLD version of policy and law.  I find that more valuable and interesting.  Good prof.  Easy class.  I recommend taking him atleast once.

Doesn't respond to emails but takes the time to send one to add him on Facebook. Incoherent rants, no structure, unfair. I emailed to meet about my exam and he refused. I gave the guy a chance despite the bad reviews and regretted it. DO NOT TAKE HIS CLASS, DO NOT WASTE YOUR TIME AND EDUCATION!!!

Stay away!!!!! He is awful. Worst professor I've had in my 4 years at U Ottawa. I was in your situation last year registering for classes and reading about Strangelove. I read some awful reviews, but I figured he couldn't be that bad so I took his class anyway. Well, turns out he is that bad. Don't make my mistake!

This guy is nuts. He is a terrible professor. I agree he's "creative" but not in an academic way. He rants, has no good information. He's teaching a course that has nothing to do with the sad outline that he produced at the beginning of the year. He's self obsessed,and so he teaches crap that has nothing to do with course. DO NOT TAKE HIS COURSES!

Horrible. Very disorganized, midterm has potential but is too unclear so it isn't fun. Lectures are practically incomprehensible. He makes us buy textbooks that we barely use and he doesn't give any semblance of assigned readings so it's not even easy to teach yourself. And I got an A in the course so trust me, I'm only bitter about wasting my time

not to mention that all of his metaphors or outside examples have to do with sex, or some sexual part of the body.i don't understand how he got a PHD, his facebook default is him with pink bunny ears on, this class hes making someone take him during his lecture. basically, if he didnt have a text he would have nothing to say besides"look at my vide

today he asked what would be useful to us from him...NOT to rant on every class about the project for the first half hour. not to read word for word from the book and to come SOMEWHAT prepared. he has no idea what he is talking about and always loses his place. he wastes an absurd amount of time and has a personality of an 11 year old boy..

Ok, I don't know why everyone bashes on this guy.  He is a really great prof - a little odd, yes - but very helpful and nice.  I love that for his midterm you have the choice of working on a paper or a video.  He allows you to be creative instead of just giving an outline for a paper.  Give this guy a chance people!!!
His lectures have no structure. Makes very uncomfortable remarks that have no relevance to the lecture.

Probably one of the smartest profs in the school, but you wouldn't know by looking at him or listening to him. One of the proffesors who lives his job yet most of the time you wish he just wrote books. His class was a drag and completly irrelevant towards anything.  in sumation. Nice guy. Bad Prof. Final word: If you have him. run!
Not uselful.

This man should not have a PHd.  The fact that he is "teaching" at a post secondary education facility is a joke.  I hated every second of my wasted time in this man's class.  He talks nothing of importance, and if this class (CMN 3174) wasn't mandatory, I would definitely not be taking it. Needless to say, I think he is the worst prof in the world

This teacher frequently goes off track of subject in class, and many times, does not cover the subject matter being studied. I also think he should revise his standards, as his Media Ethics class guidelines tell students explicitly that they can use pirated/stolen materials from the website for a video assignment. Not very ethical.
Interesting opinions are presented in his class. The internet is for ___. Watch youtube enough. Awesome professor!
Worst professor in the history of the U of O.

Addmitedly Strangelove's teaching style is less than traditional, but that is what is so fantastic about this prof.  It is because he doesn't fall in line with the status quo that he is so persecuted, he is one professor who places more importance on the value of learning and knowledge, rather than creating some class outline so students can put in

Basically he'll give you sections and page numbers of parts in the text book all throughout the course. It wont matter for any of it until the 60% final. The final is made up of all the key points he mentioned in the course. So if you went to class...Unfortunately that part is really hard to do.
horrible prof.  i wish i could take back the hours i wasted in his class.
Professors like this cheapen the quality of our undergraduate education.
Definitely the best prof in the department, after Leslie shade left. You MUST take at least one class with this guy before you graduate with a CMN degree.

I went into this class with an open mind but now I am very frustrated. I have been to every class but I always regret going; it seems like such a waste. It isn't even that I don't agree with his opinions; I am just sick of hearing them. I am having trouble taking this class seriously because of the way it is taught. Interminable communist sermon.

...for some reason i find him irritating. he talks about nothing the majority of the time, and once he didn't even bother to show up for class, sending an email saying he "felt like he wasted everyones time" but made no excuse for it. I hope he marks easy.
Hilarious guy! Come to class for the entertainment, read the text for the information.

He was crazy, and seemed like a lot of fun in the beginning. However, then he started to get anal. He would want you to have the report on certain paper, and certain type, it was rediculous. Also, are required reading was HIS BOOK! We had to write a paper on his book, that was crazy because obviously he is going to have a bias. Anyway, watch out!
What a fun prof- he's very creative and interesting. Yes, he's left-wing... but in 20 years those who complain about it will see the truth behind what he says. Very knowledgable, interesting man.

Interesting lectures. Sometimes lectures get a little off topic. As stated in class, material is presented  from a very left sided perspective. Perhaps more balance in presenting material would improve coarse however I would recommened this coarse to anyone who wants a unique class expierence.

By the time I took this course, this was my 3rd time having him as a prof and I had figured out his method.  Approach every paper from a leftist, anti-capitalist point of view and you will certainly do well.  All I can say is that I attended only 3 of his lectures in this course and finished with an A-.  He has a method; you just need to crack it.

BEST PROF EVER!!!!, makes learning the material fun and interesting and is very clear about his objectives for the papers. If you show up and do the readings you will get a good mark. Obviously the ppl that dont like him got a bad mark on their papers so dont blame him.

He is one of the worst profs that I have ever seen. Quantity of the sources seemed to be more important than the quality of the source. Not to mention he is a **** too, he always made fun made fun of other cultures except the Americans.

At first i thought this guy was crazy and wierd. But turned out that he's an AWESOME prof! He's really interested in what he teaches, and while he has problems staying on track, he knows what he's talking about. Very interesting guy and is pretty lenient
Best Prof Ever!!
to below: "the man have his love, and his love is a strange one...he must think he comes from above, here to preach us on the worth of a man..." :)
Why does the university allow people like this to teach?!! It seriously undermines the credibility of the program and our degrees. Why is this crackerpot still preaching (as opposed to teaching)?

What a boring class... don't bothering going to it... i teaches fromt he text book. you don't learn anything.. if you write an essay for him use alot of sources and footnotes and you will get an "a". Quantity of sources is more important to him then quality of work

His ideas are so weighted by left-wing bias that it is hard to sort out how much of what he is saying is legitimate and how much is propeganda. Having a bias is fine, having a bias so strong that it interferes with teaching is not. He'd make a better consipracy theorist than a professor.
He called me a redneck in the middle of class...No, I don't know why. Nuff said.

I didn't attend class for the entire last two months of the semester, and I'll probably still get an A.  With that said, I don't think I've learned a thing in the three classes I've had with this lunatic.
Too frustrating for my liking. Hands out "A"s like they're candy. Avoid him!

I can say nothing but useless.....I don't see a point in going to class when I read the textbook and he talks about nothing in it in class....I am confused by him wearing orange and his odd obsession with ****graphy and barbies...smart guy but i wouldn't survive in his head...

For those with an open mind, it is a privilege to listen to this man speak.  He rages against the machine, as more of us should.  Really cares about his students - evidenced by the extensive notes he provides on his web site re how to write and reference papers.  Come, listen, think.

This is a good prof with lots of insight. The material he presents "randomly" (like news information)is quite pertinant because it is the applied version of the theory. I appreciate this kind of illumination He's funny and entertaining, although he sometimes seems confused/spaced out.
toooooo many readings. funny guy but not recommended to take his class.
One word: FRUSTRATING.

I don't even really know what to say about this man, sure he might have a joke or two up his sleeve, but how about a theory maybe? His exam is complete crap! and I even read the textbooks...I feel like I've learned nothing, except why Barbie ended up in a wheelchair! ARGH! BAH! :|
His exams suck. He is hard to follow, jumpy.. unclear.. reads from the textbook half the time and rants about unrelated tangents the rest.

He is one funny guy, makes you laugh (he's also wierd). Not bad of a course, he explains a lot from the books, and goes on crazy tangeants about the media & media icons with his pictures. Pretty easy marker too.
Very orginal, extremely pushy on political views, makes us think. Maybe more of an entertainer than a prof. I learned to be more meticulous with my writing. Overall, bof...
Really interesting professor. Good-looking, great attitude. Sometimes a little hard on pop culture, but oh well, you still learn a lot.
No Comments
Best teacher ever. he is insane. I would marry him if he wasn't already married. And he likes good music.
No Comments
One word - weird!  Okay, he can have his entertaining moments, but not the best prof I've ever had.  Tends to be biased and close-minded.  If you don't lean left politically, watch out!

I did not like his class AT ALL - so disorganized and impossible to follow, every class I would wonder why I bothered to show up. He's nice enough but self-absorbed. I will avoid him like the plague, way too frustrating.

A most funny and entertaining 8:30 class. Very weird in a good way. People think his class is a waste of time because you don,t learn anything. However, the assignments make up for that because they are challenging and different. You learn outside of clas
Great film, great prof.
No Comments
unconventional, but makes you think!  (which is a lesser sin than being biased or irrelevant)

Dr. Strangelove is the weirdest professor in the world. He is very entertaining for his 830 am class. Some people may think that going to his class is pointless, but really it isn't..his class dicussions are awesome especially talking about our neighbour.
No Comments
All over the board, Once he came with a half shaved beard -thought I was trippin
Classes are a waste of time, don't relate to exams. Shows ineresting pics though
Gives an outline but doesn't follow it; no need to go to class
very entertaining
